Method Detail

init

public static void init(Analytics.Provider provider,
                        String apiKey,
                        boolean enabled)
Initialize the analytics system. This method should be the first called in order to handle analytics collection.

Parameters:
provider - The analytics provider to use. eg, Flurry, Localytics.
apiKey - The API Key the provider provides in order to use their service.
enabled - Whether or not analytics is currently enabled.

providerFromString

public static Analytics.Provider providerFromString(String providerString)
Retrieves the provider enumeration based on its string representation. This method is case in-sensitive.

Parameters:
providerString - The string form of a provider from the Provider enumeration.
Returns:
The enumeration element for the string or null if no provider was found.

setEnabled

public static void setEnabled(boolean en)
Turn analytics collection on/off.

Parameters:
en - Set analytics enabled status. Setting this will inhibit all calls to the underlying provider class.
